	(text "* This is a two-input power input selector.\n* If USB-C is disconnected, VBUS will be missing.\n  The base of the MOSFET will be 0V due to the\n  base resistor R11. In this configuration, the\n  MOSFET will allow VBAT to pass through, with\n  very little resistance.\n* However, if USB-C is connected, VBUS will be\n  present, and at 5V. This will make Vgs >= 0.\n  Vgs must be negative in order for the MOSFET\n  to close the path. In this configuration, the\n  only path from VBAT to BOOST_VIN is through\n  its body diode, which will not allow any\n  reverse conduction (i.e., from BOOST_VIN\n  to VBAT).\n* Thus, BOOST_VIN will be VBUS - 0.6V = 4.2V\n  (drop caused by the D11 Schottky diode) if\n  USB-C is connected, or VBAT (around 3.7V)\n  otherwise."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 1229.36 740.41 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 0.889 0.889)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "9822cd54-f794-46c8-8a52-e74a627b6935")
	)
